TACOM Website Generation Blueprint
Project Name: TACOM 2026 Redesign

Tech Stack: HTML5, CSS3 (Modern Flex/Grid), Vanilla JavaScript

Design Aesthetic: Dark Mode, Engineering HUD, High-Tech Professional

1. File Structure Requirement
Plaintext
/tacom-project
├── index.html          # Main Landing Page
├── solutions.html      # Detailed Services Page
├── cases.html          # Classic Projects Archive
├── news.html           # Technical Intelligence Feed
├── about.html          # Company History & Stats
├── contact.html        # Triage Contact Form
└── assets/             # Folder for SVG icons and Logo
2. Global Design System (CSS Variables)
Apply these to a :root selector in a global <style> tag:

Backgrounds: --bg-base: #020617;, --surface-1: #0F172A;, --surface-2: #1E293B;

Accents: --primary-glow: #60A5FA;, --accent-telecom: #FB7185;

Typography: Primary: Inter; Monospace (Data/Labels): JetBrains Mono

Borders: --glass: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);

3. Page-Specific Requirements
A. Home Page (index.html)
Hero Section: Centered text. Headline: "Leading the World Through Digital Technology". Sub-headline: "Expert Software/Hardware Outsourcing and Telecom Engineering".

Stats Bar: Include four counters: 20+ Years Experience, 500+ Clients, 98% Satisfaction, 24/7 Support.

Client Slider: Grayscale-to-color icons for China Unicom, Motorola, Nokia, and MetLife.

B. Solutions Page (solutions.html)
Grid Layout: 3-column layout featuring System Integration, Cybersecurity, and Cloud Computing.

Detail Cards: Each card needs a "Technical Spec" footer in JetBrains Mono.

C. Classic Cases (cases.html)
Impact Metrics: For each case (e.g., Manufacturing IT Upgrade or Medical Cloud Migration), include a visual progress bar or gauge showing 99.99% Continuity.

D. News Feed (news.html)
Intelligence Log: Cards for SpaceX IPO Updates and AI Dynamic Reports. Use a "Terminal Log" style with timestamps.

E. Contact Form (contact.html)
Technical Triage: A dropdown to select between System Integration and Telecom Engineering to route leads to alexwang@shtacom.com.

4. Interaction & HUD Logic
Glassmorphism: All cards must have backdrop-filter: blur(12px).

Glow Animation: On hover, cards should increase border-brightness and add a soft blue outer glow.

Responsive Menu: A mobile hamburger menu that slides in from the right with a 90% width.